00:00:05.740 --> 00:00:12.440
Behr Premium Porch and Patio Floor
Paint is an interior and exterior

00:00:12.440 --> 00:00:16.180
100-percent acrylic latex, mildew
resistant, finish

00:00:16.180 --> 00:00:20.830
that is available in to sheens: low-luster and gloss.

00:00:20.830 --> 00:00:24.130
Use on properly prepared previously
painted or prime

00:00:24.130 --> 00:00:26.980
interior or exterior surfaces.

00:00:26.980 --> 00:00:30.050
Ideal for porches, floors, decks,

00:00:30.050 --> 00:00:33.720
basements, patios, siding, trim

00:00:33.720 --> 00:00:36.820
furniture and trellises.

00:00:36.820 --> 00:00:40.690
Before you apply porch and patio floor
paint, it is essential you have a

00:00:40.690 --> 00:00:43.429
properly cleaned and prepped surface.

00:00:43.429 --> 00:00:47.429
If you have a new or uncoated surface,
please refer to the prep

00:00:47.429 --> 00:00:51.770
uncoated services for paints and stains
video.

00:00:51.770 --> 00:00:55.750
If you have a previously coated or
weathered surface, please refer to the

00:00:55.750 --> 00:00:56.160
prep

00:00:56.160 --> 00:01:00.590
coated surfaces for paints and stains
video.

00:01:00.590 --> 00:01:04.830
If you have a wood deck, porch or patio,
please refer to the prep new or

00:01:04.830 --> 00:01:07.710
weathered wood surfaces video.

00:01:07.710 --> 00:01:10.700
Now that the surface is clean, prepped
and prime,

00:01:10.700 --> 00:01:13.740
it is time to apply the porch and patio
floor paint.

00:01:13.740 --> 00:01:17.219
Please follow all label instructions.

00:01:17.219 --> 00:01:20.520
Make sure to stir before applying.

00:01:20.520 --> 00:01:24.030
Apply a thin, even coat using a 3/8 inch nap
roller cover,

00:01:24.030 --> 00:01:27.539
pad applicator, nylon polyester brush

00:01:27.539 --> 00:01:29.570
or an airless sprayer.

00:01:29.570 --> 00:01:33.190
Use the appropriate spread rate per
gallon.

00:01:33.190 --> 00:01:36.920
Spread rate varies depending on the
surfaces texture, precocity

00:01:36.920 --> 00:01:39.200
and application method.

00:01:39.200 --> 00:01:45.240
Use this product when the air and
surface temperatures are between 50°-90° F

00:01:45.250 --> 00:01:48.400
If using a roller or brush do not thin.

00:01:48.400 --> 00:01:51.600
However, if using a sprayer and thinning
is required,

00:01:51.600 --> 00:01:56.270
thin with water at a rate of no more
than 1/2 pint per gallon.

00:01:56.270 --> 00:02:00.600
If you are using more than one can,
intermix all cans of same product to

00:02:00.600 --> 00:02:03.049
ensure color uniformity.

00:02:03.049 --> 00:02:06.230
Clean-up is easy with soap and water.

00:02:06.230 --> 00:02:10.700
Allow one hour to dry to touch and four
to six hours before deciding if a second

00:02:10.700 --> 00:02:13.110
coat is necessary.

00:02:13.110 --> 00:02:17.230
Certain colors may require more than one
coat to achieve complete hide and

00:02:17.230 --> 00:02:18.879
coverage.

00:02:18.879 --> 00:02:22.620
Be sure the surface is fully cured
before use.

00:02:22.620 --> 00:02:25.770
Allow 72 hours for normal use.

00:02:25.770 --> 00:02:30.040
Allow four weeks before rinsing or
cleaning with mild detergent.

00:02:30.040 --> 00:02:34.109
Premature heavy traffic will cause paint
failure, which will require spot

00:02:34.109 --> 00:02:34.909
recoating.

00:02:34.909 --> 00:02:39.180
Be sure to wait 30 days before rinsing
or cleaning with a mild, non-abrasive,

00:02:39.180 --> 00:02:41.340
liquid detergent.

00:02:41.340 --> 00:02:45.860
We have just shown you how easy it is to
apply Behr Premium Porch and Patio Floor

00:02:45.860 --> 00:02:46.409
Paint.

00:02:46.409 --> 00:02:49.890
Enjoy your beautifully coated and
protected surface.

